('professor', 'In pragmatics, an implicature is often ___.', '["A. entailed", "B. cancelable", "C. always explicit", "D. unrelated"]'::jsonb, 'B', 1, '含意通常可撤銷 cancelable。'),
('professor', 'A performative utterance ___.', '["A. cannot be spoken", "B. can accomplish an act by being spoken", "C. must be false", "D. is always indirect"]'::jsonb, 'B', 1, '言語行為以說出即完成。'),
('professor', 'Relevance theory treats ostensive communication as ___.', '["A. purely syntactic", "B. minimizing processing effort as assumed intended", "C. avoiding inference", "D. only literal"]'::jsonb, 'B', 1, '具展示性溝通涉及最佳相關與處理成本。'),
('professor', 'In phonology, complementary distribution suggests ___.', '["A. free variation", "B. allophones of one phoneme", "C. minimal pairs", "D. tone sandhi always"]'::jsonb, 'B', 1, '互補分布常為同一音位之異音。'),
