('professor', 'Binding theory primarily regulates ___.', '["A. word order", "B. anaphor-pronoun dependencies", "C. question formation", "D. spell-out"]'::jsonb, 'B', 1, '管Binding／照應與代名詞依賴。'),
('professor', 'The EPP (Extended Projection Principle) concerns ___.', '["A. theta roles only", "B. subjects at Spec-TP", "C. phonetic transcription", "D. discourse particles"]'::jsonb, 'B', 1, 'EPP 與主語／Spec-TP 相關。'),
('professor', 'In OT syntax, higher-ranked constraints ___.', '["A. can be freely violated", "B. dominate lower-ranked ones", "C. are never evaluated", "D. apply only to morphology"]'::jsonb, 'B', 1, '優排序語法：高階限制優先。'),
('professor', 'VP ellipsis identity typically requires ___.', '["A. verbatim repetition only", "B. parallelism at the relevant structural level", "C. no licensing", "D. modal verbs"]'::jsonb, 'B', 1, 'VP 省略需結構平行。'),
('professor', 'Parasitic gaps are licensed only when ___.', '["A. no wh-movement occurs", "B. a true gap licenses wh-dependencies", "C. subjects are null", "D. infinitives are banned"]'::jsonb, 'B', 1, '寄生空缺依賴真正空缺／移位結構。'),
('professor', 'The cartographic approach maps functional heads onto ___.', '["A. single phrase", "B. fine-grained hierarchies", "C. phonetic grids", "D. random trees"]'::jsonb, 'B', 1, '製圖式句法：細緻功能層級。'),
('professor', 'In Distributed Morphology, vocabulary insertion occurs ___.', '["A. before syntax", "B. after syntax", "C. only in phonetics", "D. never"]'::jsonb, 'B', 1, '詞彙插入於句法之後。'),
('professor', 'Root suppletion mainly affects ___.', '["A. determiners", "B. exponents realizing irregular stems", "C. intonation", "D. prosodic boundaries"]'::jsonb, 'B', 1, '詞根異干替換多見於不規則詞形。'),
('professor', 'In cognitive semantics, conceptual metaphor maps ___.', '["A. sound to color only", "B. domains onto domains", "C. syntax to morphology", "D. alphabet to phonetics"]'::jsonb, 'B', 1, '概念隱喻跨域映射。'),
('professor', 'Frame semantics emphasizes ___.', '["A. rhyme", "B. knowledge structures activated by words", "C. IPA charts", "D. stress grids"]'::jsonb, 'B', 1, '框架語義：詞所喚起知識結構。'),
('professor', 'Prototype theory predicts ___.', '["A. crisp boundaries always", "B. graded category membership", "C. no polysemy", "D. uniform definitions"]'::jsonb, 'B', 1, '原型範疇具程度性。'),
('professor', 'Relevance in translation studies may prioritize ___.', '["A. word-for-word gloss only", "B. functional equivalence in context", "C. ignoring register", "D. literal cognates"]'::jsonb, 'B', 1, '功能對等／語境等效。'),
('professor', 'Skopos theory foregrounds ___.', '["A. author biography only", "B. the purpose of the translation task", "C. avoiding footnotes", "D. orthographic unity"]'::jsonb, 'B', 1, '目的論強調翻譯目的。'),
('professor', 'Corpus stylistics often relies on ___.', '["A. intuition only", "B. frequency and collocational patterns", "C. rhyme schemes alone", "D. handwritten drafts"]'::jsonb, 'B', 1, '語料庫頻率與搭配。'),
('professor', 'In narratology, focalization concerns ___.', '["A. camera lenses", "B. who perceives in the narrative", "C. chapter length", "D. typesetting"]'::jsonb, 'B', 1, '聚焦：誰在感知。'),
('professor', 'Free indirect discourse blends ___.', '["A. only dialogue tags", "B. third-person narration with character-limited perspective", "C. stage directions", "D. footnotes"]'::jsonb, 'B', 1, '自由間接引語融合敘述與角色視角。'),
('professor', 'In rhetoric, aposiopesis stops mid-utterance to imply ___.', '["A. strong emotion or discretion", "B. perfect grammar", "C. rhyme scheme", "D. IPA transcription"]'::jsonb, 'A', 0, '頓挫省略暗示強烈情感或保留。'),
('professor', 'An epic simile is characteristically ___.', '["A. one line long", "B. extended and elaborate", "C. always humorous", "D. non-metaphorical"]'::jsonb, 'B', 1, '史詩明喻冗長細緻。'),
('professor', 'Horatian satire tends to be ___.', '["A. bitter and violent", "B. urbane and tolerant", "C. purely tragic", "D. non-political always"]'::jsonb, 'B', 1, '賀拉斯式較溫和城市化。'),
('professor', 'Juvenalian satire tends toward ___.', '["A. gentle mockery only", "B. indignation and harsh attack", "C. pastoral calm", "D. pure description"]'::jsonb, 'B', 1, '朱維納爾式較激烈譴責。'),
('professor', 'Metonymy substitutes ___.', '["A. opposites", "B. a contiguous associated entity for another", "C. foreign words", "D. rhymes"]'::jsonb, 'B', 1, '借代：鄰近相關。'),
('professor', 'Synecdoche often substitutes ___.', '["A. unrelated words", "B. part for whole or vice versa", "C. synonyms only", "D. verbs for nouns"]'::jsonb, 'B', 1, '提喻：部分代整體等。'),
('professor', 'Zeugma yokes ___.', '["A. random clauses", "B. one word to two incongruous meanings", "C. only parallel nouns", "D. identical sounds"]'::jsonb, 'B', 1, '共軛／軛式搭配雙義。'),
('professor', 'Chiasmus depends on ___.', '["A. rhyme only", "B. reversed parallel structure", "C. alliteration only", "D. homophones"]'::jsonb, 'B', 1, '交錯配對 reversed parallelism。'),
('professor', 'Aporia in rhetoric signals ___.', '["A. certainty", "B. a feigned or genuine difficulty", "C. a bibliography", "D. meter"]'::jsonb, 'B', 1, '疑惑／難題 aporia。'),
('professor', 'An epistemic modal scopes over ___.', '["A. only tense", "B. the speaker''s degree of commitment", "C. only aspect", "D. only objects"]'::jsonb, 'B', 1, '認識情態：說話者確信度。'),
('professor', 'Root modals often concern ___.', '["A. pure tense", "B. permission, ability, or obligation", "C. only articles", "D. only word stress"]'::jsonb, 'B', 1, '根情態：許可能力義務等。'),
('professor', 'Scalar implicature arises from ___.', '["A. spelling rules", "B. Gricean reasoning about stronger alternatives on a scale", "C. only idioms", "D. only phonology"]'::jsonb, 'B', 1, '量級含意源於較強選項。'),
('professor', 'In acquisition research, ''more + adjective'' often evidences ___.', '["A. fossilization only", "B. movement toward comparative marking", "C. telegraphic omission only", "D. final devoicing"]'::jsonb, 'B', 1, 'more + 形 表比較結構習得。'),
('professor', 'The subset principle proposes learners prefer ___.', '["A. the largest grammar", "B. the smallest grammar consistent with input", "C. random rules", "D. borrowings"]'::jsonb, 'B', 1, '子集原則偏好較小文法。'),
('professor', 'Positive evidence typically refers to ___.', '["A. explicit correction only", "B. attested utterances learners encounter", "C. phonetic charts", "D. dictionary definitions only"]'::jsonb, 'B', 1, '正面證據：可及語料。'),
('professor', 'Negative evidence includes ___.', '["A. only praise", "B. feedback marking ungrammaticality", "C. random noise", "D. translation only"]'::jsonb, 'B', 1, '負面證據：標示不合語法。'),
('professor', 'Poverty of the stimulus arguments target ___.', '["A. behaviorist imitation only", "B. whether input suffices for acquisition as modeled", "C. only orthography", "D. only bilingual lexicons"]'::jsonb, 'B', 1, '刺激貧乏論證：輸入是否足夠。'),
('professor', 'Mirror neurons are debated regarding ___.', '["A. spelling", "B. action understanding and simulation", "C. IPA transcription", "D. tone sandhi"]'::jsonb, 'B', 1, '鏡像神經元與動作理解。'),
('professor', 'In ERP studies, N400 amplitude often indexes ___.', '["A. motor planning", "B. semantic expectancy violation", "C. pure motor reflex", "D. eye color"]'::jsonb, 'B', 1, 'N400 與語義期待違反。'),
('professor', 'LAN components are linked with ___.', '["A. only happiness", "B. syntactic morphosyntactic anomalies", "C. only musical pitch", "D. only color naming"]'::jsonb, 'B', 1, '左前負波與句法異常。'),
('professor', 'P600 is commonly associated with ___.', '["A. only breathing rate", "B. syntactic reanalysis or repair", "C. only olfaction", "D. only rhythm"]'::jsonb, 'B', 1, 'P600 與句法重分析。'),
('professor', 'In sociolinguistics, overt prestige aligns with ___.', '["A. covert norms only", "B. institutionally endorsed norms", "C. only children''s speech", "D. only slang"]'::jsonb, 'B', 1, '外顯聲望：制度化規範。'),
('professor', 'Covert prestige may valorize ___.', '["A. only formal registers", "B. local vernacular norms", "C. only spelling", "D. only loanwords"]'::jsonb, 'B', 1, '隱性聲望：在地規範。'),
('professor', 'Acts of identity theory stresses ___.', '["A. random drift", "B. speakers using language to construct selves", "C. only phonetics", "D. only etymology"]'::jsonb, 'B', 1, '語言作為身分建構。'),
('professor', 'The observer''s paradox complicates ___.', '["A. typing speed", "B. collecting natural speech while being observed", "C. only reading tests", "D. only word lists"]'::jsonb, 'B', 1, '觀察者悖論影響語料自然度。'),
('professor', 'Labovian style-shifting shows ___.', '["A. no variation", "B. attention paid to speech affects formality", "C. only borrowing", "D. only syntax"]'::jsonb, 'B', 1, '注意力影響語體轉換。'),
('professor', 'Semantic narrowing historically often yields ___.', '["A. broader meaning always", "B. more specific meanings from broader ones", "C. only synonyms", "D. only homophones"]'::jsonb, 'B', 1, '語義窄化。'),
('professor', 'Semantic widening can produce ___.', '["A. only technical jargon", "B. broader senses from narrower ones", "C. only spelling changes", "D. only stress shifts"]'::jsonb, 'B', 1, '語義擴寬。'),
('professor', 'Pejoration describes ___.', '["A. neutralization only", "B. meaning becoming more negative", "C. only vowel shifts", "D. only stress movement"]'::jsonb, 'B', 1, '貶義化。'),
('professor', 'Amelioration describes ___.', '["A. meaning becoming more positive", "B. semantic bleaching only", "C. only metaphor death", "D. only accent loss"]'::jsonb, 'A', 0, '褒義化（意義變更正面）。'),
('professor', 'Deixis anchors meaning to ___.', '["A. only dictionaries", "B. utterance context like time, place, speaker", "C. only phonemes", "D. only syllables"]'::jsonb, 'B', 1, '指示語境座標。'),
('professor', 'Analyticity in philosophy of language often pairs with ___.', '["A. thick ethical concepts only", "B. truth by virtue of meaning", "C. only empirical measurement", "D. only proper names"]'::jsonb, 'B', 1, '分析性：依意義為真。'),
('professor', 'Rigid designation (Kripke) targets ___.', '["A. all predicates", "B. referential stability across worlds for proper names", "C. only adjectives", "D. only tense"]'::jsonb, 'B', 1, '專名剛性指稱。'),
('professor', 'Two-dimensional semantics distinguishes ___.', '["A. only tense and aspect", "B. epistemic vs metaphysical intensions", "C. only orthography", "D. only syllable weight"]'::jsonb, 'B', 1, '二維語義：認識／形上內涵。'),
('professor', 'Dynamic semantics models meaning as ___.', '["A. static sets only", "B. context change potentials", "C. only phonetic strings", "D. only etymology trees"]'::jsonb, 'B', 1, '動態語義：脈絡更新潛能。'),
('professor', 'Montague grammar aims to ___.', '["A. avoid logic", "B. compose sentence meanings via systematic rules", "C. replace phonetics", "D. ban quantifiers"]'::jsonb, 'B', 1, '蒙塔古語法：系統組合意義。'),
('professor', 'Generalized quantifiers treat noun phrases as ___.', '["A. only predicates", "B. relations between sets", "C. only pronouns", "D. only determiners as heads"]'::jsonb, 'B', 1, '廣義量化詞：集合關係。'),
('professor', 'Presupposition projection investigates ___.', '["A. only spelling", "B. how complex sentences inherit presuppositions", "C. only intonation", "D. only rhyme"]'::jsonb, 'B', 1, '預設投射。'),
('professor', 'Donkey anaphora challenges ___.', '["A. only spelling rules", "B. simple treatments of indefinites and pronouns", "C. only tense", "D. only proper nouns"]'::jsonb, 'B', 1, '驢子句照應難題。'),
('professor', 'Dynamic predicate logic can represent ___.', '["A. only idioms", "B. anaphora via discourse referents", "C. only IPA", "D. only stress"]'::jsonb, 'B', 1, '動態邏輯表照應。'),
('professor', 'Situation semantics replaces possible worlds with ___.', '["A. only dictionaries", "B. situations as partial information states", "C. only syllables", "D. only rhyme schemes"]'::jsonb, 'B', 1, '情境語義：局部資訊情境。'),
('professor', 'Truthmaker semantics ties truth to ___.', '["A. only syntax trees", "B. what makes sentences true", "C. only phonetics", "D. only etymology"]'::jsonb, 'B', 1, '使真者語義。'),
('professor', 'Supervaluationism handles vagueness by ___.', '["A. banning logic", "B. quantifying over admissible sharpenings", "C. only dictionaries", "D. only homophones"]'::jsonb, 'B', 1, '超評估值：可容許細化。'),
('professor', 'Type-logical approaches link syntax and semantics via ___.', '["A. random mapping", "B. curry-howard style proofs", "C. only stress", "D. only orthography"]'::jsonb, 'B', 1, '類型邏輯／句法語義介面。'),
('professor', 'Proof-theoretic semantics privileges ___.', '["A. only dictionaries", "B. inferential rules over truth conditions alone", "C. only orthography", "D. only IPA"]'::jsonb, 'B', 1, '證明論語義：推導規則。'),
('professor', 'Lexical semantics decomposition debates whether features are ___.', '["A. always universal across languages", "B. language-particular or universal", "C. only phonetic", "D. only orthographic"]'::jsonb, 'B', 1, '詞彙分解：特徵是否普世。'),
('professor', 'Polysemy networks are often modeled as ___.', '["A. isolated lists", "B. radial categories with motivated extensions", "C. only rhyme pairs", "D. only homonyms"]'::jsonb, 'B', 1, '多義網路：放射狀範疇。'),
('professor', 'Construction grammar treats ___ as basic.', '["A. only morphemes", "B. form-meaning pairings at multiple sizes", "C. only syllables", "D. only phonemes"]'::jsonb, 'B', 1, '構式語法：多層級形義配對。'),
('professor', 'Grammaticalization typically involves ___.', '["A. only borrowing", "B. semantic bleaching and category shifts", "C. only stress movement", "D. only spelling reform"]'::jsonb, 'B', 1, '語法化：語義淡化與範疇轉移。'),
('professor', 'Grammaticalization clines suggest change is ___.', '["A. instantaneous always", "B. gradient rather than strictly abrupt", "C. only phonetic", "D. only lexical"]'::jsonb, 'B', 1, '斜坡／漸變。'),
('professor', 'Areal diffusion explains ___.', '["A. only genetic relationships", "B. similarities via contact between languages", "C. only universal grammar", "D. only orthography"]'::jsonb, 'B', 1, '區域擴散：接觸相似。'),
('professor', 'Substrate influence often surfaces in ___.', '["A. only genetic trees", "B. lexicon and phonology of a dominant language", "C. only tense", "D. only spelling"]'::jsonb, 'B', 1, '底層語影響。'),
('professor', 'Diachronic reconstruction uses ___.', '["A. only modern dictionaries", "B. the comparative method among cognates", "C. only rhyme", "D. only stress"]'::jsonb, 'B', 1, '歷史比較法。');
